<h2>üìå HTML (HyperText Markup Language)</h2>
<p><strong>What is HTML?</strong> HTML is the skeleton of a website. It tells the browser what content to show.</p>

<h3>Essential HTML Tags Explained:</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Tag</th>
<th>What It Does</th>
<th>Example</th>
<th>Purpose</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code></td>
<td>Tells browser this is HTML5</td>
<td><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code></td>
<td>Must be first line - tells browser the file type</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</code></td>
<td>Root tag for entire page</td>
<td><code>&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</code></td>
<td>Wraps all content; lang="en" means English language</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;head&gt;</code></td>
<td>Invisible section (not shown on page)</td>
<td><code>&lt;head&gt;...&lt;/head&gt;</code></td>
<td>Contains metadata, title, links to CSS files</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;title&gt;</code></td>
<td>Browser tab name</td>
<td><code>&lt;title&gt;Home - Loch Quarry&lt;/title&gt;</code></td>
<td>Shows in browser tab</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;meta&gt;</code></td>
<td>Information about the page</td>
<td><code>&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;</code></td>
<td>Gives browser instructions</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;body&gt;</code></td>
<td>Visible page content</td>
<td><code>&lt;body&gt;...&lt;/body&gt;</code></td>
<td>Everything user sees goes here</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;header&gt;</code></td>
<td>Top section (logo, nav)</td>
<td><code>&lt;header&gt;...&lt;/header&gt;</code></td>
<td>Navigation area at top</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;nav&gt;</code></td>
<td>Navigation menu</td>
<td><code>&lt;nav&gt;...&lt;/nav&gt;</code></td>
<td>Links to other pages</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;h1&gt;, &lt;h2&gt;, &lt;h3&gt;</code></td>
<td>Headings (big titles)</td>
<td><code>&lt;h1&gt;Main Title&lt;/h1&gt;</code></td>
<td>h1 = biggest, h3 = smaller</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;p&gt;</code></td>
<td>Paragraph (text)</td>
<td><code>&lt;p&gt;This is text&lt;/p&gt;</code></td>
<td>Regular paragraph text</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;button&gt;</code></td>
<td>Clickable button</td>
<td><code>&lt;button&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;</code></td>
<td>User can click to do something</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;a&gt;</code></td>
<td>Link to another page</td>
<td><code>&lt;a href="page.html"&gt;Click&lt;/a&gt;</code></td>
<td>Creates clickable link</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;section&gt;</code></td>
<td>Groups related content</td>
<td><code>&lt;section&gt;...&lt;/section&gt;</code></td>
<td>Organizes page into sections</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;div&gt;</code></td>
<td>Generic container</td>
<td><code>&lt;div&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code></td>
<td>Groups elements for styling</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>&lt;footer&gt;</code></td>
<td>Bottom section</td>
<td><code>&lt;footer&gt;...&lt;/footer&gt;</code></td>
<td>Copyright, contact info at bottom</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>üîç Meta Tags Breakdown (What's in Your &lt;head&gt;)</h2>

<h3>1. Character Encoding</h3>
<pre>&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;</pre>
<div class="highlight">
<strong>What it does:</strong> Tells browser to read special characters correctly (√©, √±, ‰∏≠Êñá, emojis üèïÔ∏è)<br>
<strong>Why it matters:</strong> Without it, text displays as garbage (‚òÉ‚ò¢‚òé)<br>
<strong>Simple explanation:</strong> Like telling someone "speak English, not Alien"
</div>

<h3>2. Viewport (for Mobile)</h3>
<pre>&lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;</pre>
<div class="highlight">
<strong>What it does:</strong> Makes page look good on phones, tablets, and computers<br>
<strong>Why it matters:</strong> Website adapts to screen size<br>
<strong>Simple explanation:</strong> Like auto-fit on a photo to fit any screen
</div>

<h3>3. Description (for Search Engines)</h3>
<pre>&lt;meta name="description" content="Loch Quarry Outdoor Center - Your destination..."&gt;</pre>
<div class="highlight">
<strong>What it does:</strong> Summary shown in Google search results<br>
<strong>Why it matters:</strong> Helps people know what your site is about before clicking
</div>

<h3>4. Author</h3>
<pre>&lt;meta name="author" content="Loch Quarry"&gt;</pre>
<div class="highlight">
<strong>What it does:</strong> Says who created the website<br>
<strong>Why it matters:</strong> Good for credit and SEO
</div>

<h2>üé® CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)</h2>
<p><strong>What is CSS?</strong> CSS makes HTML look pretty. HTML is the skeleton, CSS is the clothing and makeup.</p>

<h3>How CSS Works:</h3>
<pre>selector {
    property: value;
}</pre>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<pre>h1 {
    color: blue;
    font-size: 24px;
}</pre>
<p>This means: "Make all <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> headings blue and 24 pixels big"</p>

<h3>Essential CSS Properties You'll Use:</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Property</th>
<th>What It Does</th>
<th>Example</th>
<th>Result</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>color</code></td>
<td>Text color</td>
<td><code>color: red;</code></td>
<td>Text turns red</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>background-color</code></td>
<td>Background color</td>
<td><code>background-color: yellow;</code></td>
<td>Yellow background</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>font-size</code></td>
<td>Text size</td>
<td><code>font-size: 20px;</code></td>
<td>Text gets bigger</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>font-family</code></td>
<td>Text style</td>
<td><code>font-family: Arial;</code></td>
<td>Uses Arial font</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>width</code></td>
<td>Element width</td>
<td><code>width: 300px;</code></td>
<td>Makes element 300 pixels wide</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>height</code></td>
<td>Element height</td>
